3 B. 1. When determining the minimum salary schedule, “fringe
4 benefits” shall mean all or part of retirement benefits, excluding
5 the contributions made pursuant to subsection A of Section 17-108.1
6 of this title and the flexible benefit allowance pursuant to Section
7 26-105 of this title from the flexible benefit allowance funds
8 disbursed by the State Board of Education and the State Board of
9 Career and Technology Education pursuant to Section 26-104 of this
10 title.
11 2. If a school district intends to provide retirement benefits
12 to a teacher such that the teacher’s salary would be less than the
13 amounts set forth in the minimum salary schedule specified in
14 subsection A of this section, the district shall be required to
15 provide written notification to the teacher prior to his or her
16 employment or, if already employed by the district, no later than
17 thirty (30) days prior to the date the district elects to provide
18 retirement benefits such that the teacher’s salary would be less
19 than the minimum salary schedule.
20 C. Any of the degrees referred to in this section shall be from
21 a college recognized by the State Board of Education. The Board
22 shall accept teaching experience from out-of-state school districts
23 that are accredited by the State Board of Education state board of
24 education or appropriate state accrediting agency for the districts.
Req. No. 3704 Page 5

1 The Board shall accept teaching experience from out-of-country
2 schools that are accredited or otherwise endorsed by the appropriate
3 national or regional accrediting or endorsement authority. Out-of-
4 country certification documentation in a language other than English
5 shall be analyzed by an educational credential evaluation service in
6 accordance with industry standards and guidelines and approved by
7 the State Department of Education. The person seeking to have
8 credit granted for out-of-country teaching experience shall be
9 responsible for all costs of the analysis by a credential evaluation
10 service. The Board shall accept teaching experience from primary
11 and secondary schools that are operated by the United States
12 Department of Defense or are affiliated with the United States
13 Department of State.
14 D. For the purpose of state salary increments and retirement,
15 no teacher shall be granted credit for more than five (5) years of
16 active duty in the military service, as defined in Section 17-113 of
17 this title, or out-of-state or out-of-country teaching experience as
18 a certified teacher or its equivalent. Nothing in this section
19 shall prohibit boards of education from crediting more years of
20 experience on district salary schedules than those allowed for state
21 purposes.
22 E. The State Board of Education shall recognize, for purposes
23 of certification and salary increments, all the years of experience
24 of a:
Req. No. 3704 Page 6

1 1. Certified teacher who teaches in the educational program of
2 the Department of Corrections, beginning with fiscal year 1981;
3 2. Vocational rehabilitation counselor under the Department of
4 Human Services if the counselor was employed as a certified teacher
5 by the State Department of Education when the Division of Vocational
6 Rehabilitation was transferred from the State Board of Career and
7 Technology Education or the State Board of Education to the Oklahoma
8 Public Welfare Commission on July 1, 1968;
9 3. Vocational rehabilitation counselor which were completed
10 while employed by the Department of Human Services if such counselor
11 was certified as a teacher or was eligible for certification as a
12 teacher in this state;
13 4. Certified teacher which were completed while employed by the
14 Child Study Center located at University Hospital Oklahoma
15 Children’s Hospital, if the teacher was certified as a teacher in
16 this state; and
17 5. Certified school psychologist or psychometrist which were
18 completed while employed as a doctoral intern, psychological
19 assistant, or psychologist with any agency of this state if the
20 experience primarily involved work with persons of school- or
21 preschool-age and if the person was, at the time the experience was
22 acquired, certified as, or eligible for certification as, a school
23 psychologist or psychometrist.
24
Req. No. 3704 Page 7

1 F. The provisions of this section shall not apply to teachers
2 who have entered into postretirement employment with a public school
3 in this state and are still receiving a monthly retirement benefit.
4 G. If a school district receives either Foundation Aid or
5 Salary Incentive Aid or receives neither Foundation Aid nor Salary
6 Incentive Aid pursuant to Section 18-200.1 of this title, funds
7 appropriated for the financial support of public schools shall be
8 allocated by the State Board of Education to implement the salary
9 increases implemented beginning in the 2023-2024 school year
10 pursuant to Section 1 of Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1119 of the 1st
11 Session of the 59th Oklahoma Legislature for certified personnel
12 with zero (0) to twenty-five (25) years of experience. Funds shall
13 be allocated by January 31, 2027, and by January 31 annually
14 thereafter.
15 H. Persons employed as classroom instructional employees of
16 technology center school districts supervised by the State Board of
17 Career and Technology Education shall receive a salary increase
18 amount equal to the amount indicated in subsection A of this section
19 for the step level indicated for the person persons, provided they
20 remain employed by the same technology center school district,
21 unless the hours or the duties of the classroom instructional
22 employees are reduced proportionately.
23 H. I. Persons employed as correctional teachers or vocational
24 instructors by the Department of Corrections pursuant to Section
Req. No. 3704 Page 8

1 510. 6a of Title 57 of the Oklahoma Statutes or persons employed as
2 teachers by the Office of Juvenile Affairs shall receive a salary
3 increase amount equal to the amount indicated in subsection A of
4 this section for the step level indicated for the person persons,
5 provided they remain employed by the same Department of Corrections
6 or Office of Juvenile Affairs facility, unless the hours or the
7 duties of the correctional teachers, vocational instructors, or
8 teachers are reduced proportionately.
9 I. J. Persons employed as teachers by the State Department of
10 Rehabilitation Services shall receive a salary increase amount equal
11 to the amount indicated in subsection A of this section for the step
12 level indicated for the person persons, provided they remain
13 employed by the State Department of Rehabilitation Services, unless
14 the hours or the duties of the teachers are reduced proportionately.
15 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
16 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
17 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
18 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
19 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
